<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'line-height:26.0pt;mso-pagination:none;mso-la=
yout-grid-align:
none;text-autospace:none'>This description, like much of the <span
class=3DSpellE>Situationists</span>&#8217; practice, anticipates the emerge=
nce of
new forms of game play as art practice today, most clearly in the example of
the London-based artist collective Blast Theory.<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Blast Theory projects Can You See =
Me
Now? <span class=3DGramE>and</span> Uncle Roy All Around You <span class=3D=
SpellE>reinscribe</span><span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>urban space with the<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>rules and scenarios of their games=
.<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Can You See Me Now? <span class=3D=
GramE>players</span>
carry GPS modified devices which contain a simple graphical <span class=3DS=
pellE>Pacman</span>
style game interface displaying the location of other players in the city.
Running panicked through the city streets of Rotterdam in the first perform=
ance
of Can You See Me Now?, players tried to escape these non-corporeal pursuers
who were less restricted by the actual geographic and urban obstacles such =
as
traffic and traffic lights, pedestrians and hills.<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Similarly, Uncle Roy All <span
class=3DGramE>Around</span> You repurposed existing city infrastructure lik=
e pay
phones and car rides to play a mysterious detective style game on the stree=
ts
of London.<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Clues and game play
advance through text instructions to players' mobile computers and planted
&quot;actors&quot; (who seem like artificial intelligence players in a comp=
uter
game played by humans). Blast Theory explained: <b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-w=
eight:
normal'>The city is an arena where the unfamiliar flourishes, where the
disjointed and the disrupted are constantly threatening to overwhelm us. It=
 is
also a zone of possibility; new encounters.&quot; </b>(Blast Theory website=
,<b
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'> </b>http://www.blasttheory.co.uk/<b
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>)<o:p></o:p></b></p>

