pellE>Hiyashi's</span>
artwork can be described as <span class=3DSpellE>ludic</span> activism in
which<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>societal rules (the law=
s) are
willfully broken. Within activist culture itself, maybe since the anti WTO
demonstrations in Seattle of 1999,<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp;
</span>Dadaist humor and <span class=3DSpellE>ludic</span> activities are m=
ore
prevalent.(Brian Holmes, The Revenge of the Concept: Artistic Exchanges and
Networked Resistance, <span class=3DSpellE>Nettime</span> 2003)</p>

